# MiniView 🚀

MiniView ek Django-based web application hai jisme user authentication, profile system, follow feature, aur email OTP verification implemented hai.

---

## 🔧 Features

* User Signup / Login
* Email OTP Verification (SMTP based)
* User Profile System
* Follow / Unfollow Users
* Username Edit
* Static & Media File Handling
* Production Ready (Render Deployment)

---

## 🛠️ Tech Stack

* Backend: Django 5
* Database: SQLite (default)
* Authentication: Django Auth
* Email: SMTP (Gmail App Password)
* Deployment: Render
* Server: Gunicorn
* Static Files: WhiteNoise

---

## 📁 Project Structure

```
miniview/
│
├── app/                # Main Django app
├── miniview/           # Project settings
│   ├── settings.py
│   ├── urls.py
│   ├── wsgi.py
│
├── templates/
├── static/
├── media/
├── manage.py
├── requirements.txt
```

---

## ⚙️ Setup Instructions (Local)

### 1. Clone repo

```
git clone <your-repo-url>
cd miniview
```

### 2. Create virtual environment

```
python -m venv myenv
myenv\Scripts\activate
```

### 3. Install dependencies

```
python -m pip install -r requirements.txt
```

### 4. Run migrations

```
python manage.py migrate
```

### 5. Run server

```
python manage.py runserver
```

---

## 🔐 Environment Variables (IMPORTANT)

Never store secrets in code.

### Required variables:

```
EMAIL_HOST_USER=your@gmail.com
EMAIL_HOST_PASSWORD=your_app_password
```

---

## 📧 Gmail SMTP Setup

* Enable 2-Step Verification
* Generate App Password from Google Account
* Use that password in environment variable

---

## 🚀 Deployment (Render)

### Build Command:

```
pip install -r requirements.txt
python manage.py migrate
```

### Start Command:

```
gunicorn miniview.wsgi:application
```

### Environment Variables (Render Dashboard):

```
EMAIL_HOST_USER=your@gmail.com
EMAIL_HOST_PASSWORD=your_app_password
```

---

## ⚠️ Security Notes

* Never push `.env` file to GitHub
* Always use environment variables
* Rotate credentials if exposed

---

## 📌 Common Issues

### ❌ SMTP Authentication Error

✔ Use Gmail App Password (not normal password)

### ❌ Gunicorn Error (`app:app`)

✔ Use:

```
gunicorn miniview.wsgi:application
```

